FBIS4-64282 "drweu084_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-084 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY More on Plans More on Plans LD2904170394 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1610 GMT 29 Apr 94 LD2904170394 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Quotation marks as received] [Text] "I think that we have reached agreement over the program," said Forza Italia Leader Silvio Berlusconi following a four-hour meeting with the National Alliance leaders Gianfranco Fini and Giuseppe Tatarella, and the Northern League's leaders Umberto Bossi and Roberto Maroni. The newly appointed prime minister stressed: "We discussed the program, not ministries. The government is being formed under favorable auspices." "There are no plans" to widen the majority. Ministries will be discussed next week. Berlusconi added: "I do not think that Bossi is going to set conditions concerning the choice of ministers."
